    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 5.3 Train with Focal Loss (Class Imbalance Handler)\n",
        "\n",
        "Focal loss: **FL(p) = -α(1-p)^γ * log(p)**\n",
        "\n",
        "This down-weights easy examples (majority class) and focuses on hard ones:\n",
        "- γ=2 is typical; higher values focus more on hard examples\n",
        "- Combined with class weights (α) for best results\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Train FocalLossClassifier model\n",
        "print(\"=\" * 70)\n",
        "print(\"Training FocalLossClassifier (Focuses on Hard Examples)\")\n",
        "print(\"=\" * 70)\n",
        "\n",
        "focal_model, focal_metrics = trainer.train(\n",
        "    model_name='focal',\n",
        "    weight_decay=1e-3,\n",
        "    max_epochs=200,\n",
        "    patience=20,\n",
        "    loss_type='focal',  # Uses focal loss\n",
        "    verbose=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nFocal Loss Results:\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Test Macro F1: {focal_metrics['test_macro_f1']:.4f} (treats classes equally)\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Test Balanced Acc: {focal_metrics['test_balanced_acc']:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"  Test MAE: {focal_metrics['test_mae']:.4f} roots\")\n",
        "print(f\"  (Weighted F1: {focal_metrics['test_f1']:.4f} - for comparison only)\")\n"
